.TH man 1 "10 January 2024" "0.1" "simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- Simple shell created in C to interact with a linux operating system.

.SH SYNOPSIS
./hsh [options] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell is an sh-compatible cmd language interpreter that executes
cmds read from the standard input.

.SH Return Value

Always 0 for success, other values means failure or error.

.SH PATH

It will look inside all directions in PATH env variable for executable.

.SH

.SH OPTIONS
.B simple_shell
Command options will be typed after the main cmd followed by a space and a
 '-' symbol.

.SH EXAMPLE

[command] [options]
$ ls -l

.SH SEE ALSO
.I peerlearning(2), projectbased(2), fullstack(2), Betty(1)

.SH BUGS
Single space required after argument.

.SH AUTHOR
Osakwe Daniel.
